article.headline: Cornell 60, Yale 59
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Ryan Wittman hit two free throws in the final 32 seconds to lead Cornell in a 60-59 win over Yale Saturday night. Andrew Naeve scored 15 points and had 10 rebounds for Cornell (13-9, 6-2 Ivy). Wittman added 13 points, Alex Tyler scored 12 and Louis Dale contributed 11. Eric Flato had 18 points to lead Yale (10-11, 6-2), while Travis Pinick added 14. Cornell finished with a 51 percent shooting average, while Yale shot at 43 percent. Yale drew a foul after Wittman scored his last minute free throws, but Casey Hughes missed both of his efforts from the line. Naeve sealed the win with a rebound as time ran out. Yale had it's only lead of the game at 59-58 with less than two minutes left. Both teams finished with 31 rebounds.
